(1) & (2) (<class 'cate.core.ds.DataAccessError'>, DataAccessError('Failed to open data source "esacci.GHG.satellite-orbit-frequency.L2.CH4.SCIAMACHY.Envisat.WFMD.v4-0.r1" for given time range, region, variable names: [Errno -77] NetCDF: Access failure: b\'http://data.cci.ceda.ac.uk/thredds/dodsC/esacci/ghg/data/crdp_4/SCIAMACHY/CH4_SCI_WFMD/v4.0/2002/ESACCI-GHG-L2-CH4-SCIAMACHY-WFMD-20021001-fv1.nc#fillmismatch\''))
explanation: "Answer from Richard: The second 2 GHG files are ones which I think have come up before. As far as I remember
column7: there is a Long datatype in the file which is incompatible with the OpenDAP protocol version supported by our version of THREDDS. It is possible that updating THREDDS to use a newer version of the DAP protocol will solve this problem but we cannot do this at the moment as we need to provide WMS capabilities. WMS is not supported in newer versions of THREDDS. It is on the to-do list to look at an alternative for WMS. Once in place
column8: it would allow us to update THREDDS."

comment: (1) & (2) (<class 'cate.core.ds.DataAccessError'>, DataAccessError('Failed to open data source "esacci.GHG.satellite-orbit-frequency.L2.CO2.SCIAMACHY.Envisat.WFMD.v4-0.r1" for given time range, region, variable names: [Errno -77] NetCDF: Access failure: b\'http://data.cci.ceda.ac.uk/thredds/dodsC/esacci/ghg/data/crdp_4/SCIAMACHY/CO2_SCI_WFMD/v4.0/2002/ESACCI-GHG-L2-CO2-SCIAMACHY-WFMD-20021001-fv1.nc#fillmismatch\''))
explanation: "Answer from Richard: The second 2 GHG files are ones which I think have come up before. As far as I remember
column7: there is a Long datatype in the file which is incompatible with the OpenDAP protocol version supported by our version of THREDDS. It is possible that updating THREDDS to use a newer version of the DAP protocol will solve this problem but we cannot do this at the moment as we need to provide WMS capabilities. WMS is not supported in newer versions of THREDDS. It is on the to-do list to look at an alternative for WMS. Once in place
column8: it would allow us to update THREDDS."
